        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 1 at 6:02PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>HAZARDS...A band of heavy snow accompanied by winds of up to 50 MPH
which can rapidly reduce visibility to less than a quarter of a mile.

LOCATION AND MOVEMENT...At 601 PM MDT, a band of heavy snow was along
a line extending from 7 miles northwest of Bayfield to near Ignacio
to 9 miles northeast of Cedar Hill and moving east at 25 MPH.

LOCATIONS IMPACTED INCLUDE...
Allison, Arboles, Tiffany, Bayfield, Ignacio, and Oxford.

This includes the following highways...
U.S. Highway 160 in Colorado between mile markers 94 and 127.
Colorado 151 between mile markers 1 and 33.
Colorado 172 between mile markers 1 and 18.

SAFETY INFO...
Conditions can deteriorate rapidly in winter weather situations. Be
prepared for snow or ice covered roads. Slow down and allow extra
time to reach your destination.
</description>
